						<summary>

						<p>Stone pillar found near the old fort wall, now kept near the Ayurvedic dispensary.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1228, Vaiśākha ba. 11, Monday</hi> corresponds to 1306 A.D., May 9.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">vṛitti</hi> for offerings to god Chenna Mallīśvara of Guṟṟāla-guṁṭṭa by Vishṇu-vardhana Mahārāju.</p>						

						</summary>
